    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">a estrutura de dados do catálogo principal da biblioteca é concretizada_em o hardware do servidor HD local.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">the library main catalog data structure is concretized_in the local HD server hardware.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000059</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">De acordo com a BFO, entidades de informação não possuem massa ou extensão espacial; elas requerem um portador material para serem hospedadas. Esta relação mapeia essa dependência de hospedagem ontológica.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_expression</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Expression</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_expression</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Expressão Bibliográfica</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_expression</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">A realização intelectual ou artística específica de uma obra sob a forma de notação alfa-numérica, linguística ou textual (ex: o texto original de Dom Casmurro em português).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_expression</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">The specific intellectual or artistic realization of a work in the form of alpha-numeric, musical, or choreographic notation (e.g., the original Dom Casmurro in Portuguese text).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_item</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Item</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_item</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Item Bibliográfico</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_item</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">It is a physical, tangible, and individualized object that you can hold in your hands. It has mass, three-dimensional extension, and defined macroscopic physical boundaries in the real world.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_item</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">É o objeto físico, tangível e individualizado que você consegue segurar com as mãos. Possui massa, extensão tridimensional e limites físicos macroscópicos definidos no mundo real.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Manifestation</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Manifestação Bibliográfica</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">In the international normative standard (IFLA LRM), a Manifestation represents the ideal set of attributes of a mass-production publishing line (a model that defines the ISBN, the theoretical dimensions, and the publisher). It is not an individualized &quot;document&quot; that you read, but the conceptual recipe that the physical items follow. Therefore, preserving the conceptual purity of the MARC 21/LRM standard, it is the physical or digital embodiment of an expression, representing the product of a publishing line (it carries ideal attributes such as ISBN and publication data).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">No padrão normativo internacional (IFLA LRM), uma Manifestação representa o conjunto ideal de atributos de uma linha de produção editorial em massa (um modelo que define o ISBN, as dimensões teóricas e a editora). Ela não é um &quot;documento&quot; individualizado que você lê, mas a receita conceitual que os itens físicos seguem. Portanto preservando a pureza conceitual do padrão MARC 21/LRM, é a corporificação física ou digital de uma expressão, representando o produto de uma linha de produção editorial (carrega atributos ideais como ISBN e dados de publicação).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_record</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Record</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_record</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Registro Bibliográfico</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_record</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A strictly encoded MARC 21 record. These are not free narrative documents, but structured strings that carry information, designed to logically encode, describe, and represent a manifestation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_record</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um registro MARC 21 textualmente codificado de forma estrita. Não são documentos narrativos livres, mas strings estruturadas que carregam informação, projetada para codificar logicamente, descrever e representar uma manifestação.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_work</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Work</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_work</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Obra Bibliográfica</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_work</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A distinct intellectual or artistic creation (abstract core, e.g., the story of Dom Casmurro) that generically depends on expressions to exist in the universe.
A Work is the most abstract level of intellectual creation (the idea of ​​the story). If you translate Dom Casmurro into English, into French, or turn it into a play, the Work remains rigorously the same, although the texts (the expressions) have changed completely. The Work itself does not have fixed text characters in a language; it transcends language.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#bibliographic_work</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma criação intelectual ou artística distinta (núcleo abstrato, ex: a história de Dom Casmurro) que depende genericamente de expressões para existir no universo.
Uma Obra é o nível mais abstrato da criação intelectual (a ideia da história). Se você traduzir Dom Casmurro para o Inglês, para o Francês ou transformá-lo em uma peça de teatro, a Obra continua sendo rigorosamente a mesma, embora os textos (as expressões) tenham mudado completamente. A Obra em si não possui caracteres de texto fixados em um idioma; ela transcende a linguagem.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#catalog</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Bibliographic Catalog</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#catalog</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Catálogo Bibliográfico</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#catalog</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">An informational collection composed of structured bibliographic records organized according to cataloging rules, concretized within a catalog carrier. It is not a textbook, it is a logical and aggregated collection of individual records for inventory and search purposes, of a computational and asset-related nature.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#catalog</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Entidade informacional composta por registros bibliográficos estruturados e organizados segundo regras catalográficas, concretizada em um ou mais suportes materiais (catalog_carrier). Não é um livro texto, é uma coleção lógica e agregada de registros individuais com o propósito de inventário e busca, de natureza computacional e patrimonial.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#catalog_carrier</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Catalog Carrier</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#catalog_carrier</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Suporte do Catálogo</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#catalog_carrier</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Dispositivo físico onde reside o arquivo informacional digital (servidor/disco rígido).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#catalog_carrier</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Physical device where the digital information file resides (server/hard drive).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">MARC 21 record 123 was cataloged_by Maria (the librarian).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">o registro MARC 21 123 foi catalogado_por Maria (a bibliotecária).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Estabelece uma trilha de auditoria administrativa dentro do grafo, conectando uma entidade de informação a um agente humano atuando sob o papel de catalogador.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Establishes an administrative audit trail within the graph, connecting an information entity to a human agent acting under a cataloger role.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A relation linking a data entity (Bibliographic Record) to the physical person who authored or generated the metadata structure.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma relação vinculando uma entidade de dados (Registro Bibliográfico) à pessoa física que gerou ou foi autora da estrutura de metadados.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Catalogado por</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloged_by</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Cataloged by</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">O papel técnico que a profissional Maria desempenha no sistema enquanto realiza o tratamento de dados lógicos no formato MARC 21.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">The technical role that Maria plays in the system while processing logical data in MARC 21 format.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">As funções operacionais de catalogação dependem de um vínculo externo (contrato, designação institucional ou turno de trabalho), cessando as suas prerrogativas quando esse contexto deixa de existir.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">The operational functions of cataloging depend on an external link (contract, institutional designation, or work shift), ceasing its prerogatives when that context no longer exists.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A functional and temporary role inhering in a person within an institutional context, authorizing them to perform technical processing and metadata creation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">É o papel funcional e temporário que inere em uma pessoa dentro de um contexto institucional, autorizando-a a realizar o processamento técnico e a criação de metadados.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Cataloger Role</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloger_role</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Papel de Catalogador</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Maria cataloga a manifestação Garnier de 1899 de Dom Casmurro e cria um registro bibliográfico MARC 21.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Maria catalogs the Garnier 1899 manifestation of Dom Casmurro and creates a MARC 21 bibliographic record.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Cataloging processes transform knowledge about a manifestation into structured metadata represented in bibliographic records.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Processos de catalogação transformam conhecimento sobre uma manifestação em metadados estruturados representados em registros bibliográficos.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A documenting process in which a bibliographic manifestation is analyzed and described through the creation or modification of a bibliographic record.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Processo de documentação no qual uma manifestação bibliográfica é analisada e descrita por meio da criação ou modificação de um registro bibliográfico.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Cataloging Process</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_process</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Processo de Catalogação</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_status_specification</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">An informational specification metadata entity that declares and tracks the technical processing phase or workflow stage of a BibliographicRecord over time (In preparation, Cataloged, or Reviewed) within the library system.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_status_specification</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">É a entidade de especificação informacional (metadado) que declara e rastreia a fase de tratamento técnico ou workflow em que um BibliographicRecord se encontra no tempo (Em elaboração, Catalogado ou Revisado) dentro do sistema da biblioteca.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_status_specification</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Cataloging Status Specification</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#cataloging_status_specification</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Especificação de Status de Catalogação</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">este fluxo lógico de registro MARC 21 descreve a manifestação Garnier de 1899.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">this MARC 21 logical record stream describes the Garnier 1899 manifestation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A bibliographic record describes a manifestation by using normative schema fields (like MARC 21 tags) to capture its titles, publishing houses, and technical metadata for retrieval.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um registro bibliográfico descreve uma manifestação ao usar campos de esquemas normativos (como as tags do MARC 21) para capturar seus títulos, editoras e metadados técnicos para fins de recuperação.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A relation between a structured metadata record (Bibliographic Record) and the entity it catalogs.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma relação entre um registro de metadados estruturado (Registro Bibliográfico) e a entidade que ele cataloga.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Descreve</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#describes</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Describes</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">a manifestação editorial da Garnier de 1899 corporifica a expressão em texto original em português.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">the Garnier 1899 publishing manifestation embodies the original Portuguese text expression.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A manifestation embodies an expression by defining the commercial, physical, or technical medium parameters (such as typography, layout, or file formatting) used to deliver that expression to an audience.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma manifestação corporifica uma expressão ao definir os parâmetros comerciais, físicos ou técnicos do meio (como tipografia, layout ou formatação de arquivo) utilizados para entregar aquela expressão a um público.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A relation between a production-level informational specification (Manifestation) and the linguistic/textual entity (Expression) it packages for distribution.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma relação entre uma especificação informacional de nível de produção (Manifestação) e a entidade linguística/textual (Expressão) que ela empacota para distribuição.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Corporifica</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#embodies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Embodies</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">o livro físico em brochura na prateleira 3 com código de barras 4567 exemplifica a manifestação Garnier de 1899.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">the physical paperback book on shelf 3 with barcode 4567 exemplifies the Garnier 1899 manifestation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">An item exemplifies a manifestation when it is a physical token produced according to the characteristics defined by that manifestation blueprint, possessing unique material qualities like a barcode or inventory stamp.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um item exemplifica uma manifestação quando é um token físico produzido de acordo com as características definidas pelo plano daquela manifestação, possuindo qualidades materiais únicas como um código de barras ou carimbo de inventário.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A relation between a concrete physical artifact (Item) and the informational production blueprint (Manifestation) it materializes.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma relação entre um artefato físico concreto (Item) e o plano de produção informacional (Manifestação) que ele materializa.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Exemplifica</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Exemplifies</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Relaciona um item bibliográfico à manifestação bibliográfica que ele exemplifica.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Relates a bibliographic item to the bibliographic manifestation that it exemplifies.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Exemplifica a Manifestação</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#exemplifies_manifestation</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Exemplifies Manifestation</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">a obra bibliográfica &quot;Dom Casmurro&quot; possui_criador a pessoa &quot;Machado de Assis&quot;.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">the bibliographic work &quot;Dom Casmurro&quot; has_creator the person &quot;Machado de Assis&quot;.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Dizer que uma entidade informacional abstrata possui_criador uma pessoa física é afirmar que a pessoa executou um processo cognitivo ou físico que causou a expressão ou manifestação inicial daquela informação.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">To say that an abstract informational entity has_creator a physical person is to assert that the person executed a cognitive or physical process that caused the initial expression or manifestation of that information.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A relation between an informational content entity (such as a Work) and the physical agent (Person or Organization) responsible for its conception or creation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Uma relação entre uma entidade de conteúdo informacional (como uma Obra) e o agente físico (Pessoa ou Organização) responsável por sua concepção ou criação.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has Creator</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_creator</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Possui Criador</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A cataloging process has input a bibliographic manifestation.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um processo de catalogação tem como entrada uma manifestação bibliográfica.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Esta propriedade é usada para representar entidades disponíveis antes ou no início de um processo.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">This property is used to represent the entities available before or at the beginning of a process.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Relaciona um processo a um continuante que participa do processo como entidade de entrada.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Relates a process to a continuant that participates in the process as an input entity.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has input</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_input</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Tem entrada</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_isbn</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has ISBN</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_isbn</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Tem ISBN</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#has_isil</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has ISIL</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#has_isil</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Possui ISIL</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_isil</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Links a library organization to its normative International Standard Identifier for Libraries (ISO 15511).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_isil</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Vincula uma organização do tipo biblioteca ao seu identificador normativo internacional ISIL (ISO 15511).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#has_isni</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has ISNI</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:label"/>
        <IRI>#has_isni</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Possui ISNI</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_isni</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Links a publishing organization to its normative International Standard Name Identifier (ISO 27729).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_isni</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Vincula uma organização editorial ao seu identificador normativo internacional ISNI (ISO 27729).</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A cataloging process has output a bibliographic record.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um processo de catalogação tem como saída um registro bibliográfico.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Esta propriedade é usada para continuantes informacionais ou materiais resultantes de um processo.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">This property is used for informational or material continuants that result from a process.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Relaciona um processo a um continuante que é produzido, gerado ou resultante do processo.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Relates a process to a continuant that is produced, generated, or resulting from the process.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has output</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_output</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Tem saída</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">A loan process has participant a person who bears a reader role.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Um processo de empréstimo tem como participante uma pessoa que porta o papel de leitor.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Esta propriedade é usada para pessoas, organizações, artefatos, registros, papéis ou outros continuantes envolvidos em um processo.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty abbreviatedIRI="rdfs:comment"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">This property is used for persons, organizations, artifacts, records, roles, or other continuants involved in a process.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Relaciona um processo a um continuante que participa do processo.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Relates a process to a continuant that participates in the process.</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="en-us">Has participant</Literal>
    </AnnotationAssertion>
    <AnnotationAssertion>
        <AnnotationProperty IRI="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel"/>
        <IRI>#has_participant</IRI>
        <Literal xml:lang="pt-br">Tem participante</Literal>
